context_text:
I am a 27-years old male living alone.
I mostly work from home, so I cook most of my meals. I usually have little time or energy to do so, so I prefer to make something quick. What I care about the most is that my meals are balanced (both in micronutrients and macronutrients) and keep me full and satisfied.
I work out a lot so I consume a lot of calories. I keep track of them using an app.
I am vegetarian.
I don't mind mostly rotating through the same options over and over again. These days, I often eat:
- Pasta with legumes, some sauce;
- Hummus with crackers;
- Rice with sauteed vegetables and tofu, with soy sauce;
- Potatoes with air-fried tofu;
- Frozen vegetables with legumes and bread.

I often indulge in a night-time snack.
